1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,118
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:51,407
CHAPTER 46:
EVEN IF I HAVE TO DROP OUT

3
00:00:54,910 --> 00:00:56,745
[slurps] Mmm.

4
00:00:59,915 --> 00:01:02,001
[sighs] What time does it start?

5
00:01:03,544 --> 00:01:05,588
Was it 9:00 am?

6
00:01:06,338 --> 00:01:09,550
Insane. A disciplinary committee?

7
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:11,844
[sucks teeth] Just eat your food.

8
00:01:14,722 --> 00:01:16,140
Your novel became a big hit.

9
00:01:16,223 --> 00:01:17,558
So, what's the problem?

10
00:01:17,641 --> 00:01:18,934
Keep writing and make money.

11
00:01:19,476 --> 00:01:22,146
That way you can give me
a lot of pocket money.

12
00:01:23,063 --> 00:01:25,399
You can just drop out and take the GED.

13
00:01:31,822 --> 00:01:33,240
Your dad and I

14
00:01:33,324 --> 00:01:35,826
won't take your side
because we're your parents.

15
00:01:35,910 --> 00:01:40,164
We will accept whatever the school
decides to do about you. You understand?

16
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,124
Honey…

17
00:01:48,547 --> 00:01:50,466
[sighs]

18
00:02:00,643 --> 00:02:02,019
What's the plan today?

19
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:06,899
Shouldn't we come up with a plan together
or something?

20
00:02:08,317 --> 00:02:09,401
[sighs]

21
00:02:09,485 --> 00:02:11,403
Whatever you guys decide.

22
00:02:11,487 --> 00:02:12,488
That's right.

23
00:02:15,074 --> 00:02:17,660
I believe Eui-ju must
learn a lesson from this.

24
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,954
Especially if she intends to keep writing.

25
00:02:21,121 --> 00:02:23,248
And eventually
make a living out of it too.

26
00:02:27,211 --> 00:02:30,673
[downcast music playing]

27
00:02:30,756 --> 00:02:33,425
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

28
00:02:36,887 --> 00:02:38,931
EPISODE 15

29
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:47,731
Oh. [stammers]

30
00:02:57,116 --> 00:02:58,492
DISCIPLINARY COMMITTEE

31
00:03:12,548 --> 00:03:13,549
#GRADE HEAD - MS. JANG

32
00:03:13,632 --> 00:03:14,675
#HEAD OF STUDENT AFFAIRS
MR. SONG

33
00:03:14,758 --> 00:03:15,759
#VICE PRINCIPAL - MR. SEO

34
00:03:15,843 --> 00:03:16,885
I've asked you all here today,

35
00:03:16,969 --> 00:03:20,180
regarding Yeo Eui-ju and the novel
that she has written

36
00:03:20,264 --> 00:03:23,434
about her own teachers,
which you must've read by now.

37
00:03:23,517 --> 00:03:27,229
As you know the characters in the novel
are based on actual people, her teachers.

38
00:03:27,312 --> 00:03:29,106
And this raises concerns

39
00:03:29,189 --> 00:03:32,609
about the violation of
teachers' rights and defamation.

40
00:03:33,402 --> 00:03:36,321
Thus, I'd like your opinions
on how we should proceed with this.

41
00:03:37,072 --> 00:03:38,073
Ms. Kim,

42
00:03:38,657 --> 00:03:41,744
I was so shaken by it
that I couldn't even finish reading it.

43
00:03:42,327 --> 00:03:45,789
Oh… [chuckling]
…it was just too embarrassing.

44
00:03:45,873 --> 00:03:49,376
[clears throat] A mistake like this
can be made out of curiosity.

45
00:03:49,918 --> 00:03:53,005
And yet, she's at the stage
where her sexual identity

46
00:03:53,088 --> 00:03:56,550
as well as her own values must take root.

47
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,887
I believe adults must stop her
from taking the wrong path.

48
00:03:59,970 --> 00:04:02,056
-[tense music playing]
-Since she is still a minor,

49
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:03,974
she must be disciplined severely

50
00:04:04,558 --> 00:04:06,393
before she turns into a criminal.

51
00:04:06,477 --> 00:04:07,936
A crim…

52
00:04:08,687 --> 00:04:10,481
-A criminal?
-[clears throat]

53
00:04:10,564 --> 00:04:14,109
Ma'am, what are your thoughts then,
regarding the novel written by Eui-ju?

54
00:04:15,652 --> 00:04:16,862
Uh… [clears throat]

55
00:04:16,945 --> 00:04:21,241
Well… [sighs] …let me share a word
about this whole thing with you.

56
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:25,204
First of all, I would like to apologize
if our daughter

57
00:04:25,287 --> 00:04:28,624
has caused discomfort and concern
to any of you here today.

58
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:31,627
I only have myself to blame.

59
00:04:32,669 --> 00:04:35,881
It's… It's really all just my fault.

60
00:04:36,548 --> 00:04:40,052
I should've…
I should've paid more attention to her.

61
00:04:43,472 --> 00:04:45,307
However! [breathes shakily]

62
00:04:47,976 --> 00:04:52,731
How can a parent stop their child
from doing what they love?

63
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:58,779
Especially when their child
shares with them…

64
00:04:58,862 --> 00:05:00,114
[sincere music playing]

65
00:05:00,197 --> 00:05:04,785
…that it's the… [sighs] …the only thing
that keeps them going in life.

66
00:05:05,994 --> 00:05:08,789
She's still too young
to have a good sense of judgment.

67
00:05:08,872 --> 00:05:10,791
Please give her a chance to reflect.

68
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:13,919
-Please understand.
-[stammers] Please understand.

69
00:05:17,506 --> 00:05:18,966
Uh… [sighs]

70
00:05:19,049 --> 00:05:22,511
And now, let's hear from
the actual victims, the teachers.

71
00:05:22,594 --> 00:05:26,056
[smacks lips, sucks teeth] First of all,

72
00:05:26,932 --> 00:05:30,394
I'd like to say a word
on all of our behalf.

73
00:05:32,396 --> 00:05:34,857
Finding out the teachers
were dragged into this,

74
00:05:35,566 --> 00:05:37,317
I found that very shocking.

75
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:42,990
Mmm, and then it hit me, "Is this what
they think every time they see me?"

76
00:05:43,073 --> 00:05:45,033
That feeling was really hard to shake.

77
00:05:47,911 --> 00:05:50,747
We've given this situation
some serious thought,

78
00:05:51,415 --> 00:05:54,042
therefore, we've come to a conclusion.

79
00:05:59,631 --> 00:06:00,716
[inhales sharply]

80
00:06:01,884 --> 00:06:03,677
What do you suggest we do, Ms. Kim?

81
00:06:04,553 --> 00:06:06,680
[owl hooting plays]

82
00:06:06,763 --> 00:06:10,309
[stammers] Whatever you decide,
we're all on board ma'am.

83
00:06:11,768 --> 00:06:14,229
Oh. [chuckles]

84
00:06:14,313 --> 00:06:18,358
Uh, what about the others? [chuckles]

85
00:06:18,442 --> 00:06:20,652
I want Eui-ju to take this chance

86
00:06:20,736 --> 00:06:23,906
to understand how serious it is
to write a novel about actual people,

87
00:06:23,989 --> 00:06:25,657
especially without their consent.

88
00:06:25,741 --> 00:06:27,659
It doesn't matter
if they're turned into fiction.

89
00:06:28,243 --> 00:06:30,454
And also she must not take it lightly.

90
00:06:32,831 --> 00:06:34,249
[sighs]

91
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,959
Kill 'em with kindness, I guess.

92
00:06:36,877 --> 00:06:38,420
[inhales deeply]

93
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,631
I'll…

94
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,091
choose kindness.

95
00:06:45,177 --> 00:06:46,553
[Seo] That's ridiculous!

96
00:06:47,679 --> 00:06:51,099
If we let her slide like this,
it will destroy our school's authority.

97
00:06:51,183 --> 00:06:52,601
She must be expelled.

98
00:06:53,268 --> 00:06:55,103
Ma'am, let's expel her.

99
00:06:55,187 --> 00:06:57,522
[dramatic music playing]

100
00:07:03,028 --> 00:07:04,196
I told her to.

101
00:07:10,077 --> 00:07:11,954
I knew and I told her to keep writing it.

102
00:07:12,496 --> 00:07:14,248
It's my responsibility.

103
00:07:23,215 --> 00:07:26,426
Of course, when I first found out
I told her to delete it right away.

104
00:07:27,094 --> 00:07:28,512
I couldn't understand her.

105
00:07:29,179 --> 00:07:32,933
But Eui-ju knew what her dream was
and she was working to get closer to it.

106
00:07:33,016 --> 00:07:34,184
Her certainty…

107
00:07:36,603 --> 00:07:37,854
was very admirable.

108
00:07:41,566 --> 00:07:42,567
[groans]

109
00:07:43,277 --> 00:07:45,320
So, I just told her to keep going.

110
00:07:45,404 --> 00:07:47,572
To be there, to cheer for her,

111
00:07:48,782 --> 00:07:49,950
and to watch her grow.

112
00:07:54,663 --> 00:07:55,914
Eui-ju's a student

113
00:07:57,165 --> 00:08:00,085
who does get it done
once she puts her mind to something.

114
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:03,005
Watching her as her homeroom teacher,

115
00:08:03,088 --> 00:08:05,674
I had no choice
but to respect her persistence.

116
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:09,094
Now that we know her dream
is to be a writer,

117
00:08:09,177 --> 00:08:10,595
I'd give her a chance,

118
00:08:10,679 --> 00:08:15,434
so that her persistence…
can grow into real talent,

119
00:08:15,517 --> 00:08:19,563
and her energy and passion
can carry her all the way to her dream.

120
00:08:22,024 --> 00:08:23,025
Please understand.

121
00:08:33,035 --> 00:08:34,494
[inhales deeply]

122
00:08:34,578 --> 00:08:37,622
Let's hear from you too.
What do you say, Eui-ju?

123
00:08:38,415 --> 00:08:39,833
Are you going to keep writing?

124
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:40,959
No, right?

125
00:08:44,171 --> 00:08:45,172
I…

126
00:08:45,672 --> 00:08:46,673
Yes?

127
00:08:53,388 --> 00:08:54,389
I…

128
00:08:55,182 --> 00:08:56,183
[inhales shakily]

129
00:08:59,436 --> 00:09:02,356
[inhales shakily]
I do want to keep writing.

130
00:09:03,273 --> 00:09:04,399
[stammers] What?

131
00:09:04,941 --> 00:09:08,195
[Eui-ju breathing shakily]
I'll accept any kind of punishment…

132
00:09:08,278 --> 00:09:09,279
[hopeful music playing]

133
00:09:09,363 --> 00:09:14,201
…and from now on, I'll write on my own,
only with my own ideas.

134
00:09:14,993 --> 00:09:18,872
And honestly,
I'm truly sorry for everything that I did.

135
00:09:19,539 --> 00:09:21,583
I've already deleted We Were Friends.

136
00:09:23,710 --> 00:09:25,420
But for me writing is…

137
00:09:28,507 --> 00:09:30,467
something I want to continue doing.

138
00:09:32,677 --> 00:09:34,471
Even if I have to drop out of school…

139
00:09:36,807 --> 00:09:38,350
I will keep writing novels.

140
00:09:47,943 --> 00:09:48,944
[groans]

141
00:09:49,569 --> 00:09:50,862
[sighs]

142
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,575
I'll discuss this
with the teachers in charge first.

143
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:56,660
And…

144
00:09:58,078 --> 00:10:01,248
in four days I'll let you know
what the punishment is. Let's go.

145
00:10:07,587 --> 00:10:09,005
-[sighs]
-My apologies.

146
00:10:09,589 --> 00:10:10,632
Goodbye.

147
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:12,509
[Seo] Geez.

148
00:10:14,469 --> 00:10:15,470
[door closes]

149
00:10:16,471 --> 00:10:18,223
-I'm really sorry.
-[Da-ju] It's okay.

150
00:10:20,434 --> 00:10:25,689
Mr. Ga, I actually didn't know you were
her homeroom teacher all this time.

151
00:10:25,772 --> 00:10:26,815
It's all good.

152
00:10:27,607 --> 00:10:29,568
I should've been paying closer attention.

153
00:10:30,694 --> 00:10:33,280
-Please don't worry about it and go home.
-I see.

154
00:10:33,363 --> 00:10:34,698
Goodbye.

155
00:10:34,781 --> 00:10:36,575
I'll go speak with the principal.

156
00:10:36,658 --> 00:10:37,659
-Okay.
-Okay.

157
00:10:42,789 --> 00:10:44,124
[Ma, softly] Oh… Goodbye.

158
00:10:49,212 --> 00:10:52,090
Mom, Dad, you can… [stammers] …leave.

159
00:10:52,674 --> 00:10:53,758
Leave?

160
00:10:54,885 --> 00:10:55,886
Oh, okay.

161
00:10:55,969 --> 00:10:58,013
We'll… get going.

162
00:10:58,096 --> 00:10:59,848
See you at home.

163
00:10:59,931 --> 00:11:01,850
-[chuckles] Goodbye.
-Take care.

164
00:11:02,809 --> 00:11:03,810
Good luck in class.

165
00:11:07,397 --> 00:11:08,565
Eui-ju, back to class.

166
00:11:08,648 --> 00:11:11,026
We'll have to wait
for Mr. Ga to come back.

167
00:11:16,823 --> 00:11:18,241
I apologize for what I did.

168
00:11:20,035 --> 00:11:21,411
[both chuckle]

169
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:25,332
I didn't expect to be
in your practice novel.

170
00:11:26,082 --> 00:11:28,251
I'm so sorry, Mr. Yoon.

171
00:11:28,335 --> 00:11:29,586
[sincere music playing]

172
00:11:29,669 --> 00:11:33,256
A writer writes stories based on
what they observe and imagine,

173
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:36,593
but you must be careful
when it involves actual people.

174
00:11:37,177 --> 00:11:38,178
You understand that, Eui-ju?

175
00:11:39,304 --> 00:11:40,305
Yes.

176
00:11:40,805 --> 00:11:42,140
You know what?

177
00:11:42,224 --> 00:11:44,809
I saw this coming
when she wrote that reflection letter.

178
00:11:44,893 --> 00:11:48,355
Seriously, it had way more details
than it needed to have.

179
00:11:48,438 --> 00:11:52,484
So now I'm going to watch
how you do the Japanese essay homework.

180
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,695
And if it doesn't touch my heart
in any way,

181
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:57,280
I'll give you a flat-out F.

182
00:11:57,822 --> 00:11:58,823
-Yes.
-[chuckles]

183
00:11:58,907 --> 00:12:00,367
Poor Eui-ju. I mean…

184
00:12:00,951 --> 00:12:02,661
Mr. Jung, sorry. Because of me--

185
00:12:02,744 --> 00:12:04,079
Oh, no. Don't worry.

186
00:12:04,162 --> 00:12:05,497
I don't know much about writing anyway.

187
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:07,123
[chuckles]

188
00:12:07,207 --> 00:12:09,834
But I hear you're quite good at it.

189
00:12:10,961 --> 00:12:11,962
Huh?

190
00:12:12,045 --> 00:12:13,046
That's what matters.

191
00:12:14,464 --> 00:12:17,050
Don't worry about it, Eui-Ju.
Just go back to class.

192
00:12:18,927 --> 00:12:20,262
Yes.

193
00:12:26,768 --> 00:12:28,186
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

194
00:12:28,853 --> 00:12:32,274
No matter how I look at this,
this is straight up defamation.

195
00:12:32,357 --> 00:12:35,068
[scoffs] I just cannot let this go.

196
00:12:35,151 --> 00:12:39,155
I-I-I'm getting a lawyer
and I'm taking this all the way.

197
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:42,200
Don't worry it's just a joke, he's joking.
Go on. Go.

198
00:12:42,284 --> 00:12:45,203
I mean, why am I described
as someone so cheap, huh?

199
00:12:45,787 --> 00:12:46,788
Tell me,

200
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:50,458
do you take me for someone who hides
instead of fighting for justice?

201
00:12:50,542 --> 00:12:52,836
-You don't fight for justice.
-Not at all.

202
00:12:52,919 --> 00:12:54,129
No. It's not true, right?

203
00:12:54,212 --> 00:12:55,755
[comical music playing]

204
00:12:55,839 --> 00:12:58,383
Hey, what if people actually see me
as that kind of person?

205
00:12:58,466 --> 00:13:00,385
-[Gi-jeon] That's what you're like.
-No way.

206
00:13:00,468 --> 00:13:02,804
-You did a good job.
-You did good. Really.

207
00:13:02,887 --> 00:13:04,139
His character, it was the best.

208
00:13:04,222 --> 00:13:06,266
[chuckles] Don't listen to him.

209
00:13:06,349 --> 00:13:07,976
-Go on, Eui-ju. Go, go.
-[Dong-ju] You did well.

210
00:13:08,059 --> 00:13:10,270
Hey! You have to change it!

211
00:13:10,353 --> 00:13:11,771
Oh, come on!

212
00:13:16,359 --> 00:13:17,360
-How did it go?
-Eui-ju.

213
00:13:17,444 --> 00:13:18,612
Oh, Eui-ju.

214
00:13:18,695 --> 00:13:20,071
-How did it go?
-What did they say?

215
00:13:20,155 --> 00:13:22,490
-What did they say? Come on, tell us.
-Uh…

216
00:13:22,574 --> 00:13:24,743
-What's the verdict?
-I'm not sure yet.

217
00:13:24,826 --> 00:13:26,161
They'll let me know after the meeting.

218
00:13:26,244 --> 00:13:27,454
-Oh, no.
-What?

219
00:13:27,537 --> 00:13:30,123
Then, will the results
come out today or when?

220
00:13:30,206 --> 00:13:31,458
What did they say?

221
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:33,126
[Go-ya] And Mr. Ga, what did he say?

222
00:13:33,209 --> 00:13:35,503
Didn't he say anything? Come on, tell us.

223
00:13:36,129 --> 00:13:37,172
Actually,

224
00:13:38,048 --> 00:13:42,302
Mr. Ga already knew
because he's the one who caught me first.

225
00:13:42,385 --> 00:13:44,846
-Huh? He already knew?
-[chattering]

226
00:13:44,929 --> 00:13:47,349
-Mr. Ga?
-He said it was actually his fault

227
00:13:47,432 --> 00:13:51,603
because he's the one let me keep writing,
even after finding out about it.

228
00:13:51,686 --> 00:13:52,937
[Go-ya] He said that?

229
00:13:53,021 --> 00:13:56,024
[students gasping, whispering]

230
00:13:56,107 --> 00:13:58,360
[Dan-ji] So he actually
knew about the whole thing?

231
00:13:58,443 --> 00:14:01,196
Then…Then, what's going to happen now?

232
00:14:01,279 --> 00:14:03,114
[Eui-ju] I think
they're discussing it right now.

233
00:14:03,198 --> 00:14:04,741
[solemn music playing]

234
00:14:04,824 --> 00:14:07,827
Her novel's just as popular
as those by established writers.

235
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:12,832
In terms of books, you can say it became
a bestseller as soon as it was published.

236
00:14:13,541 --> 00:14:15,669
So what if it's that popular?

237
00:14:15,752 --> 00:14:18,088
It's downright embarrassing. [huffs]

238
00:14:18,588 --> 00:14:20,924
There was a novel by a writer
named Love Hani

239
00:14:21,007 --> 00:14:22,759
when web novels first started.

240
00:14:22,842 --> 00:14:24,594
It was harshly criticized at first,

241
00:14:24,678 --> 00:14:27,847
but then it became popular enough
to be made into a film.

242
00:14:28,431 --> 00:14:32,185
Love Hani donated part of her royalties
to her alma mater.

243
00:14:32,894 --> 00:14:34,813
Could you imagine
how proud that school was?

244
00:14:34,896 --> 00:14:36,940
She donated her royalties?

245
00:14:39,776 --> 00:14:41,611
It's still no… Unacceptable.

246
00:14:41,695 --> 00:14:43,571
What are you staring at, Mr. Song?

247
00:14:44,239 --> 00:14:46,950
[inhales sharply] Can you please tell me
what you are reading?

248
00:14:47,617 --> 00:14:49,703
Oh, gosh, Ms. Kim.

249
00:14:49,786 --> 00:14:50,912
This is actually a big deal.

250
00:14:50,995 --> 00:14:52,247
See?

251
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:54,541
I guess Eui-ju's novel is really popular.

252
00:14:54,624 --> 00:14:56,710
I mean, people are writing tons
of comments online.

253
00:14:57,293 --> 00:14:59,254
They all want to know why
she decided to leave

254
00:14:59,337 --> 00:15:00,880
and why she decided to delete the novel.

255
00:15:00,964 --> 00:15:02,674
Right, as if. [scoffs]

256
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:04,759
How many could there be?

257
00:15:04,843 --> 00:15:06,970
How many read it?
Like a thousand? [chuckles]

258
00:15:07,053 --> 00:15:10,014
[chuckles] What?
What are you talking about? Huh?

259
00:15:10,098 --> 00:15:14,853
The most recent comments alone
add up to 108,420!

260
00:15:14,936 --> 00:15:17,188
What? That many people read it?

261
00:15:17,272 --> 00:15:19,566
[amusing music playing]

262
00:15:19,649 --> 00:15:21,818
Still, it's unacceptable.

263
00:15:21,901 --> 00:15:23,695
A student using her teachers
for a novel like that.

264
00:15:23,778 --> 00:15:25,822
Oh, wow. [chuckles]

265
00:15:25,905 --> 00:15:26,906
Guess what?

266
00:15:26,990 --> 00:15:29,242
They even started a petition
under the Committee

267
00:15:29,325 --> 00:15:31,953
-so they can get Imuk to come back.
-Mr. Song!

268
00:15:34,581 --> 00:15:37,834
My biggest concern is that
our school's reputation might be damaged

269
00:15:37,917 --> 00:15:39,586
if this information gets out.

270
00:15:40,086 --> 00:15:41,629
I see it differently.

271
00:15:41,713 --> 00:15:44,841
If anything, this shows that
our school produced a student

272
00:15:44,924 --> 00:15:46,593
with actual literary talent!

273
00:15:47,177 --> 00:15:48,219
Mr. Song, please.

274
00:15:50,889 --> 00:15:51,973
[clears throat]

275
00:15:52,056 --> 00:15:53,683
This is something to be grateful for.

276
00:15:55,852 --> 00:15:58,188
She could become sensational
like what's-her-name.

277
00:15:58,271 --> 00:16:02,025
The one who wrote Harry Potter.
I mean, it's possible, right? Hmm?

278
00:16:02,609 --> 00:16:04,861
-Right. Sure.
-That's right, Ms. Kim.

279
00:16:05,945 --> 00:16:08,782
Let's see now. [breathes deeply]

280
00:16:08,865 --> 00:16:10,784
[groans] What should we do?

281
00:16:11,576 --> 00:16:13,828
[groans]

282
00:16:15,872 --> 00:16:19,209
4 DAYS LATER

283
00:16:20,627 --> 00:16:22,086
[inhales sharply]

284
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:27,383
Yeo Eui-ju's actions not only constituted
a serious violation of school rules,

285
00:16:27,467 --> 00:16:31,638
but they also had a negative impact
on all her fellow students.

286
00:16:35,558 --> 00:16:38,269
[inhales sharply]
However, given her genuine remorse

287
00:16:38,353 --> 00:16:41,648
and our belief that
she is fully capable of doing better

288
00:16:41,731 --> 00:16:44,400
we have decided to give her
one last chance.

289
00:16:45,026 --> 00:16:46,528
We will hold her accountable,

290
00:16:47,028 --> 00:16:49,614
but won't prevent her from her dreams.

291
00:16:50,323 --> 00:16:51,658
[inhales sharply]

292
00:16:51,741 --> 00:16:55,578
Therefore, Murim Girls' High School's
final decision in this matter will be…

293
00:16:55,662 --> 00:16:57,956
[dramatic music playing]

294
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,549
…suspension for five days.

295
00:17:10,677 --> 00:17:14,013
[amusing music playing]

296
00:17:19,102 --> 00:17:20,103
Anyway…

297
00:17:20,603 --> 00:17:22,063
Am I in the novel?

298
00:17:24,274 --> 00:17:26,317
-What did they say?
-How did it go? Huh?

299
00:17:26,943 --> 00:17:27,986
I'm suspended…

300
00:17:29,153 --> 00:17:30,196
for five days.

301
00:17:31,281 --> 00:17:32,323
-Suspended?
-You're suspended?

302
00:17:32,407 --> 00:17:34,701
-Suspended!
-You're only suspended?

303
00:17:34,784 --> 00:17:37,036
[squealing, cheering]

304
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,289
[triumphant, cheerful music playing]

305
00:17:39,372 --> 00:17:42,375
Hold up, should we celebrate
she's only getting suspended?

306
00:17:43,126 --> 00:17:45,044
What about college applications?

307
00:17:45,128 --> 00:17:48,631
Even with a perfect portfolio,
her record still matters.

308
00:17:48,715 --> 00:17:50,341
-Oh…
-No, no, no.

309
00:17:51,092 --> 00:17:54,178
I remember nothing stays on your record
unless it's a school violence issue.

310
00:17:54,262 --> 00:17:56,139
-Oh, really? Thank goodness.
-In any case,

311
00:17:56,222 --> 00:17:58,516
I'll have to accept it,
it's my fault after all.

312
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:03,187
Oh, come on, what could be the problem
when it's just a suspension?

313
00:18:03,271 --> 00:18:05,273
[squealing, cheering]

314
00:18:08,610 --> 00:18:09,777
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

315
00:18:09,861 --> 00:18:11,112
[clamoring]

316
00:18:12,363 --> 00:18:15,241
CHAPTER 47:
BECAUSE YOU'RE MY FIRST STUDENT

317
00:18:16,075 --> 00:18:17,994
[class] Hello.

318
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,546
I'm sure you've already heard

319
00:18:29,422 --> 00:18:30,673
that Eui-ju got suspended.

320
00:18:35,553 --> 00:18:38,222
It's only right for her
to take responsibility,

321
00:18:38,306 --> 00:18:41,351
but… I'm responsible as well.

322
00:18:42,685 --> 00:18:45,021
A teacher must always remain neutral,

323
00:18:45,647 --> 00:18:46,814
but I didn't.

324
00:18:46,898 --> 00:18:48,608
[sincere music playing]

325
00:18:49,651 --> 00:18:53,613
If this has hurt anyone's feelings,
I apologize.

326
00:18:56,115 --> 00:18:58,701
I'll try to pay more attention
to what you say,

327
00:18:58,785 --> 00:19:01,955
but I'll also ask you
to try to understand each other

328
00:19:02,038 --> 00:19:04,123
instead of arguing about
who did what wrong.

329
00:19:04,707 --> 00:19:05,917
[class] Yes, sir.

330
00:19:07,293 --> 00:19:09,087
Okay. Good luck with your classes today.

331
00:19:09,671 --> 00:19:11,297
Hey, sorry.

332
00:19:12,131 --> 00:19:13,132
Sorry.

333
00:19:13,216 --> 00:19:14,217
[door opens]

334
00:19:15,259 --> 00:19:16,386
[door closes]

335
00:19:16,469 --> 00:19:17,470
Thanks.

336
00:19:36,698 --> 00:19:37,699
What is it?

337
00:19:38,574 --> 00:19:41,619
I didn't get to thank you
for what you did for me.

338
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:43,621
Thank you, Mr. Ga.

339
00:19:45,206 --> 00:19:46,416
Don't mention it, all right?

340
00:19:48,001 --> 00:19:49,585
So… [inhales sharply]

341
00:19:49,669 --> 00:19:53,172
…Mr. Ga, why would you
do something like that?

342
00:19:54,215 --> 00:19:55,425
Like what?

343
00:19:55,925 --> 00:19:59,762
You actually convinced the principal
and all the teachers.

344
00:19:59,846 --> 00:20:02,974
And I was just wondering why you did it.

345
00:20:08,813 --> 00:20:11,566
["Why This Night" playing]

346
00:20:18,781 --> 00:20:19,824
To me, you're…

347
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,501
You are…

348
00:20:38,551 --> 00:20:39,761
my first student.

349
00:20:47,685 --> 00:20:48,770
Because…

350
00:20:50,188 --> 00:20:51,564
I'm just your student?

351
00:20:55,193 --> 00:20:57,028
Choi Ji-a, Eun Ha-su, and you,

352
00:20:57,570 --> 00:21:00,239
to me, are who actually deserve
some kindness.

353
00:21:03,576 --> 00:21:05,912
Stay away from trouble
while you're suspended.

354
00:21:05,995 --> 00:21:07,246
Go home.

355
00:21:29,268 --> 00:21:31,604
[whining]

356
00:21:31,687 --> 00:21:33,439
CHAPTER 48:
TURN OVER A NEW LEAF

357
00:21:33,523 --> 00:21:35,316
[funky, upbeat music playing]

358
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:37,902
What? You can't have this.

359
00:21:37,985 --> 00:21:40,446
[Mom] Suni, go wake your sister up.

360
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:42,657
[chuckles] Okay. All right.

361
00:21:48,788 --> 00:21:50,331
-Bang. [giggles]
-[Suni whines]

362
00:21:58,714 --> 00:21:59,715
[sighs]

363
00:22:05,263 --> 00:22:06,264
YEO EUI-JU

364
00:22:07,598 --> 00:22:09,142
[Da-ju] Mmm. Goodness.

365
00:22:15,815 --> 00:22:17,400
I'm gonna give it a try.

366
00:22:22,029 --> 00:22:26,534
I've finally decided to stop running away
before I see things through.

367
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:32,790
-What's this about?
-Who are you talking about?

368
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:36,252
[pensive music playing]

369
00:22:38,087 --> 00:22:40,715
-Going somewhere?
-[Da-ju] What is it?

370
00:22:43,259 --> 00:22:45,178
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

371
00:22:46,053 --> 00:22:48,347
-[chuckling]
-What is this?

372
00:22:48,431 --> 00:22:50,516
-I know it's supposed to be tofu…
-What is it?

373
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,851
-…but this will do.
-Oh.

374
00:22:52,476 --> 00:22:54,353
-That's true.
-Hey!

375
00:22:54,437 --> 00:22:56,564
-It's not like she came back from prison.
-Ooh.

376
00:22:56,647 --> 00:22:57,899
-Sort of similar.
-I know.

377
00:22:57,982 --> 00:22:59,734
We can say she's been discharged.

378
00:22:59,817 --> 00:23:01,277
Now go live your life right, buddy!

379
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,738
Mmm. Thanks so much, buddy.

380
00:23:03,821 --> 00:23:05,239
[students chuckling]

381
00:23:05,323 --> 00:23:06,657
-[chuckles]
-This is for you.

382
00:23:06,741 --> 00:23:07,992
Have this as you write.

383
00:23:08,075 --> 00:23:10,077
Don't let your sugar levels get too low.

384
00:23:10,995 --> 00:23:12,038
Thank you so much.

385
00:23:12,121 --> 00:23:14,665
-It's chocolate!
-Hey, don't mention it.

386
00:23:14,749 --> 00:23:17,877
Ooh! I have a GOAT writer friend!

387
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:18,961
Listen.

388
00:23:19,545 --> 00:23:21,297
-Go, Eui-ju!
-Go, Eui-ju!

389
00:23:21,380 --> 00:23:23,299
-Let's go!
-Yeah!

390
00:23:23,382 --> 00:23:25,051
[Jenny] Try some! Try some!

391
00:23:25,134 --> 00:23:26,302
[Eui-ju] Okay, okay.

392
00:23:26,385 --> 00:23:28,304
-Eat something white to start your life.
-I'll give it a try.

393
00:23:28,387 --> 00:23:31,432
[cheering] Yes! Yeah!

394
00:23:34,060 --> 00:23:36,187
[cheering, chuckling]

395
00:23:36,270 --> 00:23:37,480
Have some! Have some!

396
00:23:37,563 --> 00:23:39,899
-Give me one!
-Hey! Only one!

397
00:23:47,823 --> 00:23:48,991
You know…

398
00:23:49,825 --> 00:23:52,870
I hated that you were getting
all Mr. Ga's attention.

399
00:23:56,290 --> 00:24:00,253
I felt like maybe
he would pay more attention to me

400
00:24:00,336 --> 00:24:01,504
if I ruined you.

401
00:24:03,589 --> 00:24:05,049
But I was wrong about it.

402
00:24:07,927 --> 00:24:09,512
I'm not gonna make excuses.

403
00:24:10,930 --> 00:24:12,640
I just want to apologize to you.

404
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:15,226
I'm really sorry.

405
00:24:16,269 --> 00:24:18,604
[sincere music playing]

406
00:24:21,941 --> 00:24:23,192
[sighs]

407
00:24:24,402 --> 00:24:27,989
Thanks to you
I was able to own up to my mistakes.

408
00:24:28,948 --> 00:24:30,533
If none of this had happened,

409
00:24:30,616 --> 00:24:33,035
I would've kept writing
with all that guilt hanging over me.

410
00:24:39,125 --> 00:24:40,293
[chuckles]

411
00:24:42,336 --> 00:24:43,504
Let's get to the auditorium.

412
00:24:44,088 --> 00:24:46,507
The auditorium?
What about the morning assembly?

413
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:49,218
We have Professor Na Deul-i's
lecture today.

414
00:24:49,302 --> 00:24:52,346
By the way,
she's not Mr. Ga's girlfriend, is she?

415
00:24:52,430 --> 00:24:54,932
One, two. Testing mic, testing.
Check, one, two.

416
00:24:55,016 --> 00:24:56,892
-Say ho, ho, ho!
-[crowd] Ho, ho, ho!

417
00:24:56,976 --> 00:24:57,977
[phone buzzes]

418
00:24:59,145 --> 00:25:03,024
Dan-ji wants me to bring her
a remote control from the media room.

419
00:25:03,107 --> 00:25:05,192
-Go on without me. [chuckles]
-Okay.

420
00:25:20,416 --> 00:25:21,584
Hello.

421
00:25:22,209 --> 00:25:23,252
Oh, hello there.

422
00:25:23,919 --> 00:25:27,423
Oh! Aren't you the student
from the coffee shop the other day?

423
00:25:28,382 --> 00:25:31,052
[sighs] It's so good
to see a familiar face.

424
00:25:32,011 --> 00:25:34,597
[chuckling]
I was feeling nervous, you see.

425
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:35,681
Why?

426
00:25:36,724 --> 00:25:40,519
Well, I've hardly ever talked to
students before in my life.

427
00:25:41,354 --> 00:25:43,564
I hear students these days are scary.

428
00:25:43,647 --> 00:25:45,232
I'm worried I might make a mistake.

429
00:25:47,193 --> 00:25:48,527
The girls aren't mean.

430
00:25:49,111 --> 00:25:50,946
They won't bite you
unless you take their food.

431
00:25:51,030 --> 00:25:53,491
-[chuckling]
-[chuckles]

432
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:00,331
You came for this?

433
00:26:00,998 --> 00:26:02,458
-Yes.
-Let's go.

434
00:26:02,541 --> 00:26:04,752
[inhales deeply] Will I do a good job?

435
00:26:05,753 --> 00:26:08,130
You've lectured
bigger audiences than this.

436
00:26:08,214 --> 00:26:10,674
Ugh, I'm so nervous though.

437
00:26:11,675 --> 00:26:12,885
[groans]

438
00:26:12,968 --> 00:26:14,178
Wish me luck!

439
00:26:16,889 --> 00:26:18,391
Says someone who'll do well.

440
00:26:18,474 --> 00:26:20,851
But I've never done it
at a place like this.

441
00:26:20,935 --> 00:26:22,937
[chattering, chuckling]

442
00:26:24,730 --> 00:26:26,232
-You're cheating!
-[Jenny] I got you!

443
00:26:27,858 --> 00:26:29,026
Eui-ju.

444
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:30,611
What did she say?

445
00:26:31,362 --> 00:26:33,406
-We made up.
-You did?

446
00:26:34,073 --> 00:26:35,074
Yeah, we did.

447
00:26:35,157 --> 00:26:37,326
[applauding, cheering]

448
00:26:38,077 --> 00:26:41,247
IN MY OWN WAY,
AT A PACE THAT SUITS ME

449
00:26:43,332 --> 00:26:45,960
Hello, it's nice to meet you all.
My name is Na Deul-i.

450
00:26:46,043 --> 00:26:47,294
[funky, upbeat music playing]

451
00:26:47,378 --> 00:26:49,422
I've prepared a few slides about myself.

452
00:26:49,505 --> 00:26:50,881
Now, guess what this is.

453
00:26:50,965 --> 00:26:53,467
It's my very first test result
when I was in first grade.

454
00:26:54,427 --> 00:26:55,553
Strange, right?

455
00:26:55,636 --> 00:26:57,638
-Because I'm supposed to be a genius.
-[crowd chuckles]

456
00:26:57,721 --> 00:26:59,557
What's your standard in choosing a job?

457
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:02,184
-[students] Fame. Money.
-Fame. Money. Right, money.

458
00:27:02,268 --> 00:27:05,813
They say science students score higher
on the MBTI Thinking scale.

459
00:27:05,896 --> 00:27:08,816
The real question most of you
are probably asking right now though is,

460
00:27:08,899 --> 00:27:10,818
"Are you seriously a T right now?"

461
00:27:10,901 --> 00:27:12,111
Yes, you should give it a try too.

462
00:27:12,194 --> 00:27:14,780
At that time, everyone was pretty sure

463
00:27:14,864 --> 00:27:16,866
that the Korean team
was going to place first,

464
00:27:16,949 --> 00:27:20,494
but someone decided to drop out
right at the end,

465
00:27:20,578 --> 00:27:22,288
and the team ended up placing second.

466
00:27:22,371 --> 00:27:23,622
Guess who that was.

467
00:27:26,292 --> 00:27:29,962
It was your math teacher right there,
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

468
00:27:30,045 --> 00:27:31,922
[crowd chuckling]

469
00:27:34,925 --> 00:27:38,888
I believe that all of you will be able to
find your own answer one day.

470
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:41,015
It's so annoying

471
00:27:41,849 --> 00:27:43,225
that she's so cool.

472
00:27:43,851 --> 00:27:46,353
-[sighs]
-[Deul-i] I'll be rooting for you.

473
00:27:46,437 --> 00:27:50,065
All right. This was Na Deul-i.
Thank you for listening. Thank you.

474
00:27:58,574 --> 00:28:00,701
One, two, three.

475
00:28:01,994 --> 00:28:03,245
Go back inside now.

476
00:28:03,329 --> 00:28:06,790
[students] Thank you.

477
00:28:06,874 --> 00:28:08,125
Could you take a picture of us?

478
00:28:08,209 --> 00:28:10,169
-Mr. Ga, me too.
-Me too!

479
00:28:10,252 --> 00:28:11,378
Take one of us too!

480
00:28:12,713 --> 00:28:14,381
All right. One, two, three.

481
00:28:14,465 --> 00:28:15,758
[camera shutters]

482
00:28:16,342 --> 00:28:17,801
-Thank you.
-Mr. Ga, me too.

483
00:28:18,677 --> 00:28:19,678
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

484
00:28:19,762 --> 00:28:21,347
-One by one, yeah?
-[students] Yes!

485
00:28:21,430 --> 00:28:22,598
Oh, thank you. [chuckles]

486
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,684
-One, two, three.
-[camera shutters]

487
00:28:25,768 --> 00:28:27,561
[students chuckle]

488
00:28:27,645 --> 00:28:29,396
-One, two, three.
-[camera shutters]

489
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,731
-You're so cool.
-Thank you.

490
00:28:30,814 --> 00:28:32,775
Thank you. Thank you, thank you.

491
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:38,531
Come. Come.

492
00:28:38,614 --> 00:28:40,282
[chuckles]

493
00:28:40,366 --> 00:28:41,784
All right. One, two, three.

494
00:28:41,867 --> 00:28:43,285
[camera shutters]

495
00:28:44,495 --> 00:28:45,496
[both] Thank you.

496
00:28:46,163 --> 00:28:49,124
I got to relax and pull it off
all thanks to you.

497
00:28:49,208 --> 00:28:50,626
-I really appreciate it.
-[chuckles]

498
00:28:51,835 --> 00:28:53,754
I was able to relax thanks to her.

499
00:28:56,966 --> 00:28:59,009
The after-school class
will have a pop quiz today.

500
00:28:59,093 --> 00:29:00,344
Write it on the blackboard.

501
00:29:00,427 --> 00:29:02,054
-Yes, sir.
-Go on.

502
00:29:02,721 --> 00:29:04,056
-Goodbye.
-Bye-bye now.

503
00:29:05,224 --> 00:29:07,810
-Let's go.
-[students chuckling]

504
00:29:07,893 --> 00:29:09,186
-Did you take it?
-Yeah.

505
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:10,604
[chuckles]

506
00:29:13,065 --> 00:29:16,235
Whoa, they do make a great couple.

507
00:29:20,072 --> 00:29:21,115
Sorry.

508
00:29:24,201 --> 00:29:25,327
[sighs]

509
00:29:25,411 --> 00:29:26,662
Yeah, I know.

510
00:29:27,371 --> 00:29:29,373
He belongs with her and not me.

511
00:29:33,836 --> 00:29:34,837
Let's go.

512
00:29:36,922 --> 00:29:39,425
Happy you stayed for the research
instead of going to the States?

513
00:29:39,508 --> 00:29:43,637
CHAPTER 49:
THE ABSOLUT VALUE OF ROMANCE

514
00:29:43,721 --> 00:29:45,681
So, does that mean we're rivals now?

515
00:29:46,932 --> 00:29:48,142
Who will be first?

516
00:29:48,767 --> 00:29:51,145
I mean, who will find the proper answer.

517
00:29:52,938 --> 00:29:55,566
Yeah, I guess time will tell

518
00:29:56,317 --> 00:29:58,652
if math on its own has any value at all.

519
00:29:59,153 --> 00:30:00,446
[scoffs]

520
00:30:00,529 --> 00:30:02,114
You'll regret it when it's too late.

521
00:30:05,117 --> 00:30:06,410
Go on.

522
00:30:06,994 --> 00:30:09,538
[smacks lips] All right fine.
I'm leaving, okay? [scoffs]

523
00:30:10,581 --> 00:30:12,166
-Bye.
-Bye!

524
00:30:13,500 --> 00:30:15,961
VISITOR PARKING LOT

525
00:30:28,974 --> 00:30:31,060
[class] Hello, Mr. Ga.

526
00:30:31,143 --> 00:30:32,686
All right, there's a pop quiz today.

527
00:30:32,770 --> 00:30:34,605
You have 20 minutes
to solve the questions.

528
00:30:34,688 --> 00:30:35,689
Pass these back.

529
00:30:53,374 --> 00:30:54,833
PAST MATH EXAM QUESTIONS

530
00:30:55,959 --> 00:30:59,546
[pensive music playing]

531
00:31:01,298 --> 00:31:02,424
3. PROPERTIES
OF LOGARITHMIC FUNCTIONS

532
00:31:02,508 --> 00:31:03,509
2. MEAN VALUE THEOREM

533
00:31:03,592 --> 00:31:04,843
1. DIFFERENTIATION
OF POLYNOMIAL FUNCTION

534
00:31:13,352 --> 00:31:14,353
[exhales shakily]

535
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:20,734
[sniffs]

536
00:31:30,994 --> 00:31:32,913
If you're done,
submit it and you can leave.

537
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,322
Stop and bring it over.

538
00:32:12,035 --> 00:32:13,036
Bring it over.

539
00:32:36,643 --> 00:32:37,728
Leave it here and go home.

540
00:33:03,796 --> 00:33:06,673
[hopeful music playing]

541
00:33:20,312 --> 00:33:24,358
[Eui-ju] Absolute value refers
to something that exists solely as itself

542
00:33:24,441 --> 00:33:27,027
without being compared to
any other object.

543
00:33:27,569 --> 00:33:30,364
A state where no conditions
or constraints are attached

544
00:33:30,447 --> 00:33:32,115
and nothing can stand against it.

545
00:33:32,199 --> 00:33:35,077
Find the absolut value
of the following romance.

546
00:33:39,081 --> 00:33:42,543
What is the absolut value of
glasses divided by pigeon

547
00:33:42,626 --> 00:33:45,128
multiplied by the square root
of emergency room

548
00:33:45,212 --> 00:33:48,298
plus the square
of after-school class plus novel

549
00:33:48,382 --> 00:33:50,300
multiplied by the limit of bus stop?

550
00:34:18,996 --> 00:34:22,374
ABSOLUTE
ABSOLUTE

551
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:24,918
-Seriously?
-Can't you even spell it right?

552
00:34:27,004 --> 00:34:28,463
I know how to spell it.

553
00:34:29,423 --> 00:34:30,591
This is just

554
00:34:31,174 --> 00:34:35,804
a literary device I used
to emphasize the word "absolute."

555
00:34:37,139 --> 00:34:38,265
[sighs]

556
00:34:38,348 --> 00:34:41,018
Both your spelling
and your equation are a mess.

557
00:34:41,935 --> 00:34:43,353
Is there an answer?

558
00:34:43,437 --> 00:34:46,148
Of course! This is the only problem
I've been working on lately.

559
00:34:46,857 --> 00:34:48,275
What's the answer then?

560
00:34:49,943 --> 00:34:50,944
I've got…

561
00:34:52,279 --> 00:34:53,614
only one answer.

562
00:34:54,781 --> 00:34:55,782
[sighs]

563
00:34:58,035 --> 00:34:59,119
To me…

564
00:35:05,083 --> 00:35:06,084
To me,

565
00:35:07,085 --> 00:35:08,128
the answer is…

566
00:35:15,969 --> 00:35:17,596
This absolut value…

567
00:35:21,725 --> 00:35:23,185
The value is you.

568
00:35:24,728 --> 00:35:26,647
[tender music playing]

569
00:35:28,398 --> 00:35:30,400
My absolut value of romance…

570
00:35:32,194 --> 00:35:33,779
is you, Mr. Ga.

